          "systemMessage": "You are a TV sports news scriptwriter. Write a short, energetic news-anchor script about the given topic that runs about 20 seconds when read aloud (roughly 55-70 words).\n\nRules:\n- Output ONLY the words the anchor speaks \u2014 one flowing paragraph.\n- No stage directions, no timestamps, no camera notes, no speaker labels, no markdown, no quotation marks around the whole thing.\n- Start with a warm welcome, deliver the key update with excitement, and end with a hook to keep watching.\n- Keep it broadcast-natural and easy to say."
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        -96,
        0
      ],
      "id": "22222222-2222-4222-8222-222222222222",
      "name": "Write Script (Ollama)"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "model": "gemma4:latest",
        "options": {}
